headline: Carnival's EBITDA Momentum Picks Up: Is Margin Expansion Sustainable?
summary: CCL's yield gains and onboard spend surge lift fiscal second-quarter margins, prompting a boost to FY25 EBITDA guidance.

headline: 3 Reasons to Sell NCLH and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: What a brutal six months it’s been for Norwegian Cruise Line. The stock has dropped 21.8% and now trades at $20.26, rattling many shareholders. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
